“You don't ask for a lighter rucksack, you build up stronger shoulders." Truer words have never been spoken.

We are proud to introduce former Green Beret @jasonjmccarthy and the organization he founded: @goruck. These guys understand that human beings are built to live outside their comfort zone, that we're meant to push our mind, body, and spirit to the limits. GORUCK provides that opportunity in a community of like-minded individuals who are passionate about LIFE in all of its hardships and victories.

@greenberetfoundation 
@tenthsfg

HUNTING: One of the best possible forms of father-son bonding. Coffee fuels the body, but it's moments like these that fuel the soul.

@brcc_ed took down that beautiful bull at 230 yards. The man is in his 70s and he's still a BEAST. He embodies that no-excuse love for the outdoors that's an essential part of the BRCC spirit — even though @evanhafer is the one taking his dad hunting this time around, it's obvious where Evan's love for the outdoors comes from.

We can't say enough about the contributions that Ed has made to Black Rifle Coffee over the years. He really is an essential part of the beating heart of BRCC.

Having great coffee along for the ride just makes these incredible experiences that much better, but you have to be able to make coffee ANYWHERE. Making coffee to be consumed on-the-go, like our Coffee Steep Bags or Black Rifle Instant Coffee, is an artform, honestly. We're also passionate about making gear for the trip as well — from our @yeti tumblers to our all-in-one Long Range Carry Kits.

@loganstark @brcc_outdoors

Ever been in a near ambush over sweet deals on coffee? Because we have.

Tag TWO FRIENDS in the comments here and we'll randomly choose 100 people to get a case of RTD and a gift certificate to Bass Pro. GO GO GO!

Oh, and YES! You can grab Black Rifle Coffee at whatever Bass Pro Shops or Cabela’s you choose. NO! You will not actually get ambushed (sorry, guys).

When we had the idea of making a video IN a Bass Pro Shops location — a part of us didn’t realize they’d actually say YES. Despite our usual destruction, they were super gracious and amazing every step of the way. Shout out to Corridor Digital for helping us put this thing together as well.

